# Hermes ACP Provider – AionUi Configuration Reference
#
# This patch documents how Hermes is configured as an ACP backend in AionUi.
# In production, this is handled automatically by:
#   1. Pre-installing hermes-agent[acp] (puts `hermes` CLI on PATH)
#   2. AionUi auto-detecting `hermes` via `command -v hermes`
#   3. ACP_BACKENDS_ALL environment variable
#
# No manual patching is required. This file is for reference only.

# --- AionUi config injection (file-based, written at startup) ---
# AionUi reads config from /data/config/aionui-config.txt (base64 JSON)
#
# Equivalent config for manual setup:
#
# ACP_BACKENDS_ALL=hermes
#
# Or in aionui-config.txt (base64 of):
# {
#   "acp": {
#     "backends": {
#       "hermes": {
#         "name": "Hermes",
#         "cliCommand": "hermes",
#         "acpArgs": ["acp"],
#         "env": {
#           "ACP_BACKENDS_ALL": "hermes"
#         }
#       }
#     }
#   }
# }
